         <abstract>
            <p>When computing a partial differential equation, it is often necessary to introduce artificial boundaries. Here we explain a systematic method to obtain boundary conditions for the wave equation in one dimension, fitting to the discretization scheme and stable. Moreover, we give error estimates on the reflected part.</p>
          </abstract>
